CapabilityStatement - Birth and Fetal Death

description.value: This section describes the expected capabilities of a BFDR Document producer actor who is responsible for producing clinical documents and a BFDR Document consumer who receives and consumes the clinical documents.

name.value: Bundle - Document Birth Report

description.value: This Bundle profile represents a Birth Document Bundle. It contains any one of the Birth Report Compositions.

name.value: Bundle - Document Fetal Death Report

description.value: This Bundle profile represents a Fetal Death Document Bundle. It contains any one of the Fetal Death Compositions.

name.value: Bundle - Document Demographic Coded Content

description.value: This bundle profile contains instances of the resources comprising demographic (race and ethnicity) coded content. This bundle is information-content equivalent to the traditional NCHS [MRE](https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/dvs/200XMOR_web_with%20clearance%20revisions-acc.pdf)/NRE format.

name.value: Bundle - Document Coded Cause of Fetal Death

description.value: This bundle profile contains instances of the resources comprising cause of fetal death coded content.

name.value: Composition - Provider Fetal Death Report

description.value: This Composition profile contains constraints to address the use case describing the need for fetal death information to be recorded and communicated to the jurisdictional Vital Records Office.

name.value: Composition - Provider Live Birth Report

description.value: This Composition profile defines constraints to address the use case in which information for live birth information is recorded and communicated to the jurisdictional Vital Records Office.

name.value: Composition - Jurisdiction Fetal Death Report

description.value: This Composition profile contains information of a fetal death and the creation of a jurisdictional file to be recorded and communicated to the national statistics agency.

name.value: Composition - Jurisdiction Live Birth Report

description.value: This Composition profile contains information of a live birth and the issuance of a Birth Certificate to be recorded and communicated to the national statistics agency.

name.value: Composition - Coded Cause of Fetal Death

description.value: This profile communicates coded cause of fetal death information to appropriate jurisdictional Vital Records Offices.

name.value: Composition - Coded Race and Ethnicity

description.value: This Composition profile communicates coded race and ethnicity information to the appropriate jurisdictional Vital Records Office, along with the submitted input race and ethnicity information.

name.value: Questionnaire - Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate

description.value: This Questionnaire represents the [Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate](https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/dvs/moms-worksheet-2016-508.pdf).

name.value: Questionnaire - Patient's Fetal Death Worksheet

description.value: This Questionnaire represents the [Patient's Worksheet for the Report of Fetal Death](https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/dvs/fetal-death-mother-worksheet-english-2019-508.pdf).

name.value: Encounter - Birth

description.value: This Encounter profile represents the child's birth encounter.

name.value: Encounter - Maternity

description.value: This Encounter profile represents the mother's maternity encounter.

name.value: Birth and Fetal Death Location

description.value: Location used for source/destination of transfers and location of birth. Includes all standard extensions

name.value: Encounter Maternity Reference

description.value: This Extension profile is a reference to the maternity encounter.

name.value: Practitioner - Birth Attendant

description.value: The attendant at birth is defined as the individual at the delivery who is responsible for the delivery.

name.value: Practitioner - Birth Certifier

description.value: Certifier (USCorePractitioner) used in BFDR

name.value: Practitioner Role - Birth Attendant

description.value: Used to indicate that an instance relates to the birth attendant.

name.value: Practitioner Role - Certifier

description.value: Used to indicate that an instance relates to the birth certifier.

name.value: Observation - APGAR Score

description.value: APGAR score post-birth. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Birth Weight

description.value: The weight of the infant/fetus at birth/delivery. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Fetal Presentation at Birth/Delivery

description.value: This Observation profile represents the fetal presentation (orientation within the mother's womb) of a fetus prior to delivery/birth. Only the presentations in the preferred binding can be reported to NCHS. The full set of abnormal presentations is included to support more general use.

name.value: Observation - Gestational Age at Delivery

description.value: The obstetric estimate of the infant’s gestation in completed weeks based on the birth/delivery attendant’s final estimate of gestation which should be determined by all perinatal factors and assessments such as ultrasound, but not the neonatal exam. For submission to NCHS, values in days will be divided by 7 without remainder, and values in weeks will be rounded down to an integer.

name.value: Observation - Infant Breastfed at Discharge

description.value: This profile represents whether or not the infant was being breastfed at discharge.

name.value: Observation - Infant Living

description.value: An indication of whether the infant is living at the time the report is being submitted. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Mother Delivery Weight

description.value: The weight of the mother at the time of birth/delivery. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Number of Fetal Deaths This Delivery

description.value: The number of fetal deaths in this delivery. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Number of Live Births This Delivery

description.value: The number of live births in this delivery. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Condition - Seizure

description.value: This Condition profile indicates the newborn had an abnormal condition of seizure.

name.value: Observation - NICU Admission

description.value: This profile indicates that the abnormal condition of an admission to the NICU was present. NOTE: this may be better modeled as an Encounter.

name.value: Procedure - Antibiotic for Suspected Neonatal Sepsis

description.value: This profile represents an abnormal condition of antibiotic given for suspected neonatal sepsis.

name.value: Procedure - Assisted Ventilation Following Delivery

description.value: This profile represents an abnormal condition of the newborn of assisted ventilation immediately following delivery.

name.value: Procedure - Assisted Ventilation More Than Six Hours

description.value: This profile represents an abnormal condition of the newborn of assisted ventilation for more than six hours.

name.value: Procedure - Surfactant Replacement Therapy

description.value: This profile represents an abnormal condition of the newborn of surfactant replacement therapy.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Abnormal Conditions of Newborn

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified abnormal conditions of the newborn were present.

name.value: Condition - Congenital Anomaly of Newborn

description.value: This Condition profile represents information on whether the infant suffered from one or more of a list of known malformations diagnosed prenatally or after delivery.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Congenital Anomolies Of The Newborn

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified congenital anomolies of the newborn were present.

name.value: Condition - Chorioamnionitis

description.value: This Condition profile indicates a labor and delivery characteristic of chorioamnionitis.

name.value: Observation - Antibiotics Administered During Labor

description.value: This Observation profile indicates a characteristic of labor of antibiotics administered during labor.

name.value: Observation - Administration of Steroids for Fetal Lung Maturation

description.value: This Observation profile indicates a characteristic of labor of administration of steroids for fetal lung maturation.

name.value: Procedure - Augmentation of Labor

description.value: This Procedure profile indicates a characteristic of labor of augmentation of labor.

name.value: Procedure - Epidural or Spinal Anesthesia

description.value: This Procedure profile indicates a characteristic of labor of epidural or spinal anesthesia.

name.value: Procedure - Induction of Labor

description.value: This Procedure profile indicates a characteristic of labor of induction of labor.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Characteristics of Labor and Delivery

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified characteristics of labor and delivery were present.

name.value: Coverage - Principal Payer for Delivery

description.value: This Coverage profile represents the principal payer for this delivery.

name.value: Observation - Cigarette Smoking Before and During Pregnancy

description.value: This profile represents the average number of cigarettes smoked per day for each time period indicated by the value selected for code.

name.value: Observation - Date of First Prenatal Care Visit

description.value: This profile represents the date of the first prenatal care visit for this pregnancy. A prenatal visit is where a physician or other health care professional examined and/or counseled the pregnant woman for the pregnancy. If this profile is not present it indicates that the mother did not receive prenatal care at any time during the pregnancy.

name.value: Observation - Date of Last Live Birth

description.value: This profile represents the date of the mother's last live born infant (do not include this birth).

name.value: Observation - Date of Last Other Pregnancy Outcome

description.value: This profile represents the date of the mother's last other pregnancy outcome (includes pregnancy losses of any gestational age, e.g., spontaneous or induced losses or ectopic pregnancies) (do not include this birth).

name.value: Observation - Last Menstrual Period

description.value: This profile represents the date of the last menstrual period of the patient. The first day of last menstrual period should be captured. The effectiveTime captures the observation date. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Mother Height

description.value: The height of the mother. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Mother Prepregnancy Weight

description.value: The weight of the mother before becoming pregnant. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Mother Recieved WIC Food

description.value: This profile represents whether or not the mother made use of the Women, Infants and Children (WIC) nutritional program during the pregnancy.

name.value: Observation - Number of Births Now Dead

description.value: The total number of previous live-born infants for the mother now dead. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Number of Births Now Living

description.value: The total number of previous live-born infants for the mother now living. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Number of Other Pregnancy Outcomes

description.value: The total number of other pregnancy outcomes for the mother that did not result in a live birth (included pregnancy losses of any gestational age, e.g., spontaneous or induced losses or ectopic pregnancies). Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Number of Prenatal Visits

description.value: The total number of prenatal visits for the mother. The dates of the first and last prenatal visit are indicated by the effective date range. If the mother received no prenatal care, the value should indicate 0 visits. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Condition - Infection Present During Pregnancy

description.value: This Condition profile represents infections present and/or treated during the pregnancy.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Infections During Pregnancy

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified infections during pregnancy were present.

name.value: Observation - Labor Trial Attempted

description.value: This Observation profile represents whether, in the case of a cesarean delivery, a trial of labor was attempted.

name.value: Observation - Number of Previous Cesareans

description.value: The total number of prior cesarean deliveries for the mother. Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Procedure - Obstetric

description.value: This profile represents information about a particular medical treatment or invasive/manipulative procedure that was performed during this pregnancy specifically in the treatment of the pregnancy, management of labor and/or delivery.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Obstetric Procedures

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified obstetric procedures were present.

name.value: Procedure - Final Route and Method of Delivery

description.value: This profile represents the final route and method of delivery.

name.value: Observation - Unknown Final Route and Method of Delivery

description.value: Unknown Final route and method of delivery as defined by the US Standard Certificate of Live Birth (2003) and US Standard Fetal Death Report (2003). If delivery is cesarean, trial of labor is also recorded.

name.value: Condition - Eclampsia Hypertension

description.value: This Condition profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of eclampsia hypertension.

name.value: Condition - Gestational Diabetes

description.value: This Condition profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of gestational diabetes.

name.value: Condition - Gestational Hypertension

description.value: This Condition profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of gestational hypertension.

name.value: Condition - Prepregnancy Diabetes

description.value: This Condition profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of prepregnancy diabetes.

name.value: Condition - Prepregnancy Hypertension

description.value: This Condition profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of prepregnancy hypertension.

name.value: Observation - Previous Cesarean

description.value: This profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of previous cesarean.

name.value: Observation - Previous Preterm Birth

description.value: This Observation profile indicates that the mother had a pregnancy risk factor of previous preterm birth.

name.value: Procedure - Artificial Insemination

description.value: This Procedure profile records that a pregnancy risk factor of artificial insemination was provided to the mother.

name.value: Procedure - Assisted Fertilization

description.value: This Procedure profile records that a pregnancy risk factor of assisted fertilization was provided to the mother.

name.value: Procedure - Infertility Treatment

description.value: This Procedure profile records that a pregnancy risk factor of infertility treatment was provided to the mother.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Pregnancy Risk Factors

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified pregnancy risk factors specifiable in this IG (73775-9) are present.

name.value: Condition - Perineal Laceration

description.value: This Condition profile indicates a maternal morbidity of perineal laceration.

name.value: Condition - Ruptured Uterus

description.value: This Condition profile indicates a maternal morbidity of ruptured uterus.

name.value: Observation - ICU Admission

description.value: This profile indicates that the maternal morbidity of an admission to the ICU was present. NOTE: this may be better modeled as an Encounter.

name.value: Procedure - Blood Transfusion

description.value: This Procedure profile indicates a maternal morbidity of a blood transfusion.

name.value: Procedure - Unplanned Hysterectomy

description.value: This Procedure profile indicates a maternal morbidity of unplanned hysterectomy.

name.value: Observation - None Of Specified Maternal Morbidities

description.value: This profile indicates that none of the specified maternal morbidities were present.

name.value: Condition - Fetal Death Cause or Condition

description.value: This Condition profile contains information provided by the clinician to indicate the cause or causes of the fetal death.

name.value: Condition - Fetal Death Other Cause or Condition

description.value: This Condition profile represents another significant cause or condition for the death of the fetus.

name.value: Observation - Autopsy or Histological Exam Results Used

description.value: This profile represents whether or not the results of a performed autopsy or a performed histological placental examination were used as part of determining the cause of death.

name.value: Observation - Coded Initiating Fetal Death Cause or Condition

description.value: This profile represents the coded initiating cause/condition of fetal death.

name.value: Observation - Coded Other Fetal Death Cause or Condition

description.value: This profile represents a coded other significant cause/condition of fetal death.

name.value: Observation - Fetal Death Time Point

description.value: This Observation profile represents the estimated time of fetal death; the time of death is characterized by the relationship to the time of delivery.

name.value: Observation - Fetal Remains Disposition Method

description.value: This Observation profile represents the method of disposition of the deceased fetus.

name.value: Observation - Histological Placental Exam Performed

description.value: This profile represents whether or not a histological placental examination was performed.

name.value: Patient - Decedent Fetus

description.value: A stillborn for whom clinical data is included in the report.

name.value: Observation - Mother Married During Pregnancy

description.value: This profile represents whether or not the mother was married at conception, at the time of birth, or at any time between conception and giving birth.

name.value: Observation - Paternity Acknowledgement Signed

description.value: This Observation represents whether or not a paternity acknowledgement was signed by the father if the mother was not married at conception, at the time of birth, or at any time between conception and giving birth.

name.value: Observation - Social Security Number Requested For Child

description.value: This Observation profile represents whether or not a social security number has been requested for the child. If a social security number was requested, set valueBoolean=true and enter the time requested in the effectiveDateTime data element.

name.value: Observation - Birth Plurality of Pregnancy

description.value: The number of fetuses delivered live or dead at any time in the pregnancy regardless of gestational age, or if the fetuses were delivered at different dates in the pregnancy. This profile is not explicitly mapped to an IJE value and supports encoding plurality as a characteristic of pregnancy (outside of the core BFDR use case). Migrated from VRCL.

name.value: Observation - Planned to Deliver at Home

description.value: This Observation profile represents whether or not a home birth was planned for the infant.

name.value: Birth Edit Flags

description.value: This code system contains codes to represent edit flags specific to BFDR. Additional edit flag codes are located in [CodeSystemEditFlagsVitalRecords](https://hl7.org/fhir/us/vr-common-library/2024Jan/CodeSystem-CodeSystem-vr-edit-flags.html)

name.value: Local BFDR Codes

description.value: Local Codes for concepts in BFDR that lack an appropriate LOINC or SCT code

name.value: APGAR Score Timing

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent standard timings for APGAR assessments.

name.value: Birth and Fetal Death Financial Class

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent birth and fetal death financial class. This valueset is based on [PHVS_BirthAndFetalDeathFinancialClass_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=D20CD804-8487-E311-AE2A-0017A477041A). using codes from the [Source of Payment Typology](https://terminology.hl7.org/3.0.0/CodeSystem-SOPT.html) codesystem.

name.value: Birth Attendants Titles

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent the type of birth attendant titles. This valueset is based on [PHVS_BirthAttendantTitles_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=7B108BDB-5F50-482F-9E9D-643EC75364A2)

name.value: Birth Delivery Occurred

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent the type of place where birth or delivery occurred. This valueset is based on [PHVS_BirthDeliveryOccurred_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=BC64CB23-8210-4CE0-B2AE-F45169BBDC51)

name.value: Birth Weight Edit Flags (NCHS)

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Birth Weight Edit Flags. This valueset is based on [PHVS_BirthWeightEditFlags_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=FA7A83A3-FCFD-E611-A856-0017A477041A)

name.value: Cigarette Smoking Before and During Pregnancy

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent the number of cigarettes smoked in specific periods before and during pregnancy.

name.value: Delivery Routes

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Delivery Routes. This valueset is based on [PHVS_DeliveryRoutes_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=0C9E4D45-3FFD-4E97-AEF3-18CE5B878F46)

name.value: Estimate of Gestation Edit Flags (NCHS)

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Estimate of Gestation Edit Flags. This valueset is based on [PHVS_EstimateOfGestationEditFlags_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?oid=2.16.840.1.114222.4.11.7567)

name.value: Fetal Death Cause or Condition

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent fetal death cause or condition. This valueset is based on [PHVS_FetalDeathCauseOrCondition_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=DC1C6A94-C9FF-42CD-B546-E789003ED793).

name.value: Fetal Death Time Points

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent fetal death time points. This valueset is based on [PHVS_FetalDeathTimePoints_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=52F8C812-2C70-4038-8F0F-D6E0532D4EBD)

name.value: Fetal Presentations

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent fetal presentations. This valueset is based on [PHVS_FetalPresentations_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=3C696B7B-BB33-4818-8996-1E3461E3F512). Only these codes are supported for exchange with NCHS.

name.value: Fetal Remains Disposition Method

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Fetal Remains Method of Disposition. This valueset is based on [PHVS_FetalRemainsDispositionMethod_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?oid=2.16.840.1.114222.4.11.7585). It differs from the [MethodOfDispositionVS] valueset in that includes 'Hospital Disposition', but not 'Entombment'.

name.value: Histological Placental Examination

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent histological placental examinations. This valueset is based on [PHVS_HistologicalPlacentalExamination_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=82BF4C7F-D01F-4019-A1E1-9F7CAACB7FC6)

name.value: Infections During Pregnancy Live Birth

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Infections During Pregnancy Live Birth. This valueset is based on [PHVS_InfectionsDuringPregnancyLiveBirth_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=AEF5A3D4-960C-4194-8BB6-392C7282D216). Includes 'Other' value for general utility, although #OTH is not allowed for birth submissions to NCHS.

name.value: Informant Relationship to Mother

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent informants relationship to mother. This valueset is based on [PHVS_InformantRelationshiptoMother_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=ADF95682-912A-E711-BE3F-0017A477041A).

name.value: Location Types

description.value: Valueset for location types used to differentate transfer and birth locations

name.value: Fetal Presentations - Max

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent fetal presentations. It expands on the [FetalPresentationsVS] by including intensionally all codes for abnormal presentations, as suggested by [FHIR-44554](https://jira.hl7.org/browse/FHIR-44554).

name.value: Newborn Congenital Anomalies

description.value: The valueset contains codes to represent newborn congenital anomalies. This valueset is based on [PHVS_NewbornCongenitalAnomalies_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=BC64CB23-8210-4CE0-B2AE-F45169BBDC51). Includes 'Other' value for general utility, although #OTH is not allowed for birth submissions to NCHS.

name.value: Number of Previous Cesareans Edit Flags (NCHS)

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Number of Previous Cesareans Edit Flags. This valueset is based on [PHVS_NumberOfPreviousCesareansEditFlags_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=C5BC6D8B-DDFA-E611-A856-0017A477041A)

name.value: Pregnancy Report Edit Flags (NCHS)

description.value: This valueset contains codes to represent Pregnancy Report Edit Flags. This valueset is based on [PHVS_PregnancyReportEditFlags_NCHS](https://phinvads.cdc.gov/vads/ViewValueSet.action?id=BD25B456-85EC-45D7-B578-1024EE2920F4). Used for MothersHeight, MothersDeliveryWeight, MothersPrepregnancyWeight, NumberPrenatalCareVisits

name.value: Obstetric Procedure Outcome

description.value: This valueset contains codes that represent the successful or unsuccessful outcome of an obstretric procedure

name.value: Units of Gestational Age

description.value:
This valueset contains the set of codes for specifying the units used when recording gestational age (days, weeks.).
Reporting to NCHS is always in units of weeks, but other users of the associated [ObservationGestationalAgeAtDelivery](StructureDefinition-Observation-gestational-age-at-delivery.html) profile may want to record days.
